<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="461" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1341,1942]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1341,1366]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[283,401,1341,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelinidae" genus="Coccobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[283,401,1341,1365]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="461">Coccobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[902,1039,1341,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Aphelinidae</taxonomicName>
by the following features. Female with antenna 
<number box="[304,317,1377,1402]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="7.0">7</number>
-segmented, including 
<number box="[576,588,1377,1402]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="3.0">3</number>
-segmented funicle and 
<number box="[861,874,1377,1402]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="2.0">2</number>
-segmented clava, often with some segments pale and others brown to dark brown, thus forming a distinct colour pattern; male with antenna 
<number box="[1159,1171,1413,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="8.0">8</number>
-segmented, funicle not differentiated from clava. Mid-lobe of mesoscutum large, with numerous setae; axillae small, widely separated, not advanced anteriorly of transscutal articulation, and both with a single seta; mesoscutellum usually with 
<number box="[1310,1324,1486,1510]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="2.0">2</number>
or 
<number box="[1361,1375,1486,1510]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="3.0">3</number>
pairs of setae, rarely more than 
<number box="[453,467,1522,1546]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="3.0">3</number>
pairs. Fore wing usually hyaline, without linea calva, often with narrow (sometimes relatively broad) asetose area posterobasally; postmarginal vein absent or very short. Tarsal formula 
<number box="[1276,1293,1557,1582]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="5.0">5</number>
: 
<number box="[1297,1314,1557,1582]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="5.0">5</number>
: 
<number box="[1318,1335,1557,1582]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="5.0">5</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="461" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1341,1942]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461">
<taxonomicName box="[199,317,1593,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelinidae" genus="Coccobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,317,1593,1617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="461">Coccobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is close to 
<taxonomicName authority="De Santis 1940" authorityName="De Santis" authorityYear="1940" box="[458,777,1593,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelinidae" genus="Prophyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[458,588,1593,1617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="461">Prophyscus</emphasis>
De Santis 
<number box="[721,777,1594,1618]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="1940.0">1940</number>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[839,996,1593,1617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="461">Idiococcobius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hayat" box="[1006,1144,1594,1618]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" refString="Hayat, M. &amp; Khan, F. R. (2010) Additions to the Aphelinidae of India (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea): 1. On species of Ablerus Howard, Coccobius Ratzeburg, Coccophagus Westwood, Pteroptrix Westwood, and Idiococcobius Hayat gen. nov. Colemania, 21, 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="2010">
Hayat 
<number box="[1084,1144,1594,1618]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[1158,1288,1593,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelinidae" genus="Prophyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1158,1288,1593,1617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="461">Prophyscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[151,269,1629,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelinidae" genus="Coccobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,269,1629,1653]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="461">Coccobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly in the presence of parascutella, and females having a very short ovipositor and males an enormously enlarged scape (
<bibRefCitation author="Hayat" box="[481,621,1666,1690]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" refString="Hayat, M. (1998) Aphelinidae of India (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea): a taxonomic revision. Memoirs on Entomology, International, 13, 247 - 257." type="journal article" year="1998">
Hayat 
<number box="[561,621,1666,1690]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[644,800,1665,1689]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="461">Idiococcobius</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[960,1078,1665,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelinidae" genus="Coccobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[960,1078,1665,1689]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="461">Coccobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly in the mid-lobe of the mesoscutum having six pairs of setae arranged in bilateral symmetry, the fore wing being long and narrow with the long marginal fringe only slightly shorter than the wing width, and the submarginal vein having 
<number box="[1225,1239,1738,1762]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="1.0">1</number>
or 
<number box="[1276,1290,1738,1762]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="2.0">2</number>
setae (
<bibRefCitation author="Hayat" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" refString="Hayat, M. &amp; Khan, F. R. (2010) Additions to the Aphelinidae of India (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea): 1. On species of Ablerus Howard, Coccobius Ratzeburg, Coccophagus Westwood, Pteroptrix Westwood, and Idiococcobius Hayat gen. nov. Colemania, 21, 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="2010">
Hayat 
<number box="[151,212,1774,1798]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1341,1942]" pageId="1" pageNumber="461">
Generally, characters used to separate species of 
<taxonomicName box="[771,889,1809,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelinidae" genus="Coccobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[771,889,1809,1833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="461">Coccobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
include different combinations of body colour patterns, colour pattern and relative lengths of the antennal segments, the number of setae on the mid-lobe of the mesoscutum and mesoscutellum, characteristics of the reticulate sculpture on the mesonotum, and relative length of the ovipositor.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
